      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide14-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Fundamental & Powerful Concept: Critical Thinking" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide14-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s14-1", "content": [{ "text": "Critical thinking is "}, { "text": "thinking about your thinking", "bold": true }, { "text": ", while you're thinking, in order to achieve "}, { "text": "better", "bold": true }, { "text": " thinking (Paul & Elder, 2006)." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s14-2", "content": [{ "text": "Critical thinking is "}, { "text": "reflective", "bold": true }, { "text": ", involves "}, { "text": "standards", "bold": true }, { "text": ", is "}, { "text": "authentic", "bold": true }, { "text": " and involves being "}, { "text": "reasonable", "bold": true }, { "text": " (Nosich, 2012, pp. 3-4)." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s14-3", "content": [{ "text": "When a medical doctor examines a patient and conducts medical tests, the process is "}, { "text": "active and systematic", "bold": true }, { "text": " and results in a correct diagnosis." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s14-4", "content": [{ "text": "Critical thinking is like a "}, { "text": "pair of binoculars", "bold": true }, { "text": "—they allow you to get up close, explore details, put what you see in "}, { "text": "context and understand more", "bold": true }, { "text": " of what you are seeing (Nosich, 2012, p. 34)." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide15-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Steps in the Critical Thinking Research Process" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide15-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": true,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s15-1", "content": [{ "text": "Define your research question." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s15-2", "content": [{ "text": "Research your topic." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s15-3", "content": [{ "text": "Consider all arguments." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s15-4", "content": [{ "text": "Tentatively commit to a position." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s15-5", "content": [{ "text": "Determine your thesis." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s15-6", "content": [{ "text": "Begin writing OR revisit Step 2." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide16-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Structure of a Research Article (Diagram)" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide16-img",
        "type": "image",
        "src": "/data/research-methods-se/rmse-chap2-literature-review/images/slide16_article_structure.png",
        "alt": "Funnel diagram showing the structure of a research article: Abstract, Introduction, Methods, Results, Discussion, References.",
        "caption": [{ "text": "Typical structure of a research article." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "Structure of a Research Article (Detailed)" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-h3-struct",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Structure of an article" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-p-struct",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "The journal articles mostly follow the format of abstract, introduction, methods, results, discussion, conclusion, and bibliography." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-h3-abs",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Abstract (Summary)" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-p-abs",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "A concise summary of the article, including methodology, results and their implications, authors' interpretations and conclusions." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-h3-intro",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Introduction (Why)" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-p-intro",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "The authors introduce their topic, explain the purpose of the study, and present the statement of the research hypothesis. There is also a brief overview of the other literature that has been written about the same topic." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-h3-methods",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Methods/Methodology / Materials (How)" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-p-methods",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "It provides the technical details of how the study was conducted, the identification of participants, procedures, and materials." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-h3-results",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Results (What Happened)" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-p-results",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "Includes the data the authors use to reach their conclusions. These are often presented in figures, tables and graphs." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-h3-discuss",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Discussion / Analysis / (What It Means)" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-p-discuss",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "The authors analyse the data, evaluate whether the results of their study answered their hypothesis and explain how results support the conclusions." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-h3-concl",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Conclusion (What Was Learned)" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-p-concl",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "Here the authors offer their final thoughts about how the study adds to the existing knowledge on the topic, the strengths and weaknesses of the study, and recommendations for future research." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-h3-ref",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "References" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide17-p-ref",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [{ "text": "A list of sources cited in the journal article." }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide18-h2",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 2,
        "content": [{ "text": "How to Conduct a Literature Review: Steps" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide18-h3-proc",
        "type": "heading",
        "level": 3,
        "content": [{ "text": "Process:" }]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide18-list",
        "type": "list",
        "ordered": false,
        "items": [
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s18-1", "content": [{ "text": "Define Scope: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Narrow to specific SE topics (e.g., \"AI in software testing\")." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s18-2", "content": [{ "text": "Search: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Use databases (IEEE Xplore, ACM DL) with keywords (\"agile AND productivity\")." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s18-3", "content": [{ "text": "Evaluate Sources: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Check relevance, credibility, and publication date." }] },
          { "id": "rmse-c2-sm-li-s18-4", "content": [{ "text": "Synthesize: ", "bold": true }, { "text": "Group findings by theme (e.g., \"success factors for open-source collaboration\")." }] }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "rmse-c2-sm-block-slide18-q",
        "type": "alert",
        "style": "info",
